classDiagram
    class Cell {
        -int row
        -int column
        -CellState state
        +Cell(row, column)
        +getState() CellState
        +setState(state) void
        +isEmpty() boolean
        +getRow() int
        +getColumn() int
    }

    class Board {
        -Cell[][] cells
        -int size
        +Board(size)
        +getCell(row, col) Cell
        +placeSymbol(row, col, symbol) boolean
        +isFull() boolean
        +display() void
        +reset() void
    }

    class Player {
        -String name
        -Symbol symbol
        -int wins
        +Player(name, symbol)
        +getName() String
        +getSymbol() Symbol
        +getWins() int
        +incrementWins() void
    }

    class CellState {
        <<enumeration>>
        EMPTY
        X
        O
        +toString() String
        +getDisplay() String
    }

    class Symbol {
        <<enumeration>>
        X
        O
        +toString() String
        +getCellState() CellState
    }

    Board "1" *-- "9" Cell : contains
    Cell --> CellState : has state
    Player --> Symbol : has symbol

    note for CellState "Type-safe representation of cell contents.
    Prevents invalid values like 'A' or 'x'.
    EMPTY, X, or O are the only options"

    note for Symbol "Type-safe representation of player symbols.
